82-year-old male death tests positive for MERS-CoV infection
------------------------------------------------------------
The Department of Health and Human Services announces the death of an 82-year-old male on 3 Jun 2015 who tested positive for MERS-CoV infection.

The patient had underlying disease -- asthma, bacterial pneumonia, fever and respiratory distress following hospitalization since 9 May 2015 death for treatment. Patient was in the same room as patient no. 16 between 28-30 May 2015.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This unfortunate fatality was in a tertiary case -- 3rd generation case. According to the MOH report, the individual had significant underlying disease, a contributing factor known to lead to more serious disease with MERS-CoV infections. - Mod.MPP]

