[3] South Korea, 5 new cases, total cases 41, including 4 deaths - MOH update 5 Jun 2015
Date: Fri 5 Jun 2015
Source: South Korean Ministry of Health [in Korean, machine transl., edited]
http://www.mw.go.kr/front_new/al/sal0301vw.jsp?PAR_MENU_ID=04&MENU_ID=0403&page=1&CONT_SEQ=323027


In the past 24 hours there have been 5 newly confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection including 1 death.

Of the 5 newly confirmed cases, 3 were in hospital B between 14-27 May 2015, 20-28 May with case 9, and 22-28 May with case 14 in the same ward.

The other 2 cases included one from hospital F 14-31 May 2015 in same hospital room as case no. 16, and the other visited the emergency room of hospital D where case 14 was admitted.

In addition, there was a fatality among a previously reported 76-year-old male who was in hospital B 15-17 May 2015 at the same time the index case was there. He deteriorated on 4 Jun 2014. He was initially admitted to the hospital with the diagnosis of cholangiocarcinoma, asthma, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease.

Listing of newly confirmed cases [includes case 36 who was confirmed on 4 Jun 2015, and cases 37-41 who were confirmed 5 Jun 2015]:

36: 82-year old male / 4 Jun 2015 / 28-30 May 2015 hospital roommate of case no. 16, fatality
37: contact with index case
38: contact at same hospital as index case
39: contact at same hospital as index case
40: contact with case no. 16
41: contact with case no. 14

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[At the time of preparation of this report, the MOH line listing of 5 Jun 2015 newly confirmed cases was not available and the above list was generated using a sub-optimal machine translation of a description of the newly confirmed cases. In summary, since the last MERS-CoV update published on ProMED-mail, there have been an additional 6 cases reported. One was a fatal case diagnosed post-mortem (the 82-year-old male with significant underlying disease) who had been a roommate of case no. 16. Of the other 5 cases, 3 were secondary cases who had been admitted to hospital B at the same time as the index case, one had been a contact with case no. 16 in hospital F and the other had been a contact in the emergency room at hospital D where case no. 14 was admitted. In addition, a 76-year-old male who had previously been confirmed (case no. 3 from the S. Korean MOH line listing). The 76-year-old fatality was in an individual with severe cholangiocarcinoma, asthma, and chronic obstructive pulmonary diseases.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of South Korea can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3411121,195. - Mod.MPP]

