[5] Saudi Arabia, 1 new case, 1 new fatality - MOH 4 Jun 2015
Date: Thu 4 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-06-04-001.aspx


As of today, 4 Jun 2015, there have been a total of:
1019 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
450 deaths,
563 recoveries, and
6 currently active cases including 2 cases on home isolation.

Information on newly confirmed case:
Hufoof: 64-year-old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker, currently in stable condition, history of possible contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or community is currently under review.

Information on newly reported fatality:
Hufoof: 27-year-old expat female, non-healthcare worker, history of pre-existing co-morbidities. [Reported by MOH as newly confirmed case on 29 May 2015, at which time was noted to be in critical condition. At time of initial report was noted to have had contact with another case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[It appears as though the outbreak in Hufoof is ongoing with a total of 23 cases reported in Hufoof since 20 Apr 2015.

Information on the most recent reported cases on 2 and 3 Jun 2015 became available today:
2 Jun 2015: A 45-year-old Saudi male non-healthcare worker from Hufoof, noted to be in stable condition. A history of possible contact with other case(s) is currently under review.
3 Jun 2015: A 50-year-old expat male healthcare worker from Hufoof was noted to be in stable condition, and gave a positive history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community.

Information on the most recent reported fatalities on 2 and 3 Jun 2015:
2 Jun 2015: A 54-year-old Saudi male non-healthcare worker with a history of pre-existing co-morbidities, had been reported as newly confirmed on 1 Jun 2015, at which time he was noted to be admitted to the ICU in critical condition. History of possible contact with other case(s) was under review.
3 Jun 2015: A 43-year-old Saudi male non-healthcare worker with a history of pre-existing co-morbidities, had been reported as newly confirmed on 30 May 2015, at which time he was noted to be in critical condition. He did have a history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or in the community.

With the addition of the new case and fatality report of today -- 4 Jun 2015 -- the total number of MERS-CoV cases reported by Saudi Arabia is now at 1019 including 450 deaths -- the reported case fatality rate observed in Saudi Arabia is now 44.2 percent. And the total number of cases reported by Hufoof since 20 Apr 2015 is 23.

A map showing the location of Hufoof can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

